Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:11.56,Main,,0,0,0,,"Chiffon Cake"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.06,0:00:12.82,Main,,0,0,0,,"Cheesecake"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.40,0:00:21.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Did I wake you? I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:22.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.90,0:00:27.01,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll catch a cold sleeping there, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.01,0:00:31.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I know. But I wanted to read\Na little more of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.08,0:00:31.88,Main,,0,0,0,,"Cheesecake"\NI know. But I wanted to read\Na little more of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:35.05,Main,,0,0,0,,"Cheesecake"\NI want to be like you and Mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.05,0:00:36.01,Main,,0,0,0,,"Cheesecake"\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.01,0:00:36.85,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.85,0:00:39.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Will I be able to, if I read lots of books?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.35,0:00:41.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.59,0:00:46.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Then you just have to think about\Na lot of things and try them yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.79,0:00:48.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Think?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.43,0:00:52.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. Humans create what they imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.56,0:00:54.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Imagine?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.20,0:00:57.54,Main,,0,0,0,,It means producing the things\Nyou dream about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.84,0:01:02.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Food and science are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.94,0:01:04.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.33,0:02:39.74,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 1\NGilbert the Sage"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:48.55,Main,,0,0,0,,It's so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.55,0:02:53.39,Main,,0,0,0,,It's got ricotta cheese in it\Ntoday, huh? It's so fluffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:56.56,Main,,0,0,0,,You got it! Your palate is\Nas impressive as ever, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.56,0:02:58.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Cake is so fluffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:03:00.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now, Rika.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.39,0:03:04.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Being born a pâtissier's daughter\Nmakes me happy as a clam!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:07.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy as a clam!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.20,0:03:13.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I wish Papa could have some of this, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.97,0:03:19.31,Main,,0,0,0,,He's like me. He gets so into\Nhis work, he forgets to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.31,0:03:22.15,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder what he's off doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.15,0:03:24.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Aren't you worried, Mama?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.42,0:03:28.72,Main,,0,0,0,,The day after our wedding, I lost\Ncontact with him for two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:31.86,Main,,0,0,0,,I was certainly worried then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:34.36,Main,,0,0,0,,That's my papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:37.00,Main,,0,0,0,,But the lack of contact\Nis proof that he's doing okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:38.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:51.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm off, Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.61,0:03:56.28,Main,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.68,0:03:59.68,Main,,0,0,0,,"Incorporated Sekiei Academy\NAobadai Middle School"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.49,0:04:04.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.62,0:04:05.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.33,0:04:08.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.83,0:04:09.79,Main,,0,0,0,,C-Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.79,0:04:13.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's going on, Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.73,0:04:17.00,Main,,0,0,0,,What's with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.00,0:04:21.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Waka? Some kind of secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.37,0:04:23.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, you're good at cooking, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.98,0:04:25.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:29.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is Futa's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.05,0:04:31.62,Main,,0,0,0,,What? It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.08,0:04:36.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever. Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:38.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he's in the soccer club, as you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:44.16,Main,,0,0,0,,I was thinking he might like a big,\Nround cake shaped like a soccer ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.16,0:04:46.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow, that sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:50.00,Main,,0,0,0,,But when I tried to make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:56.11,Main,,0,0,0,,It was too thick to cook\Nthrough properly, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.11,0:04:59.64,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd had a great idea for once...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.64,0:05:02.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Then why not make a miniature version?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:06.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.72,0:05:13.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka Mizuki must do everything\Nboldly and grandly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.89,0:05:19.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if it's just a cake\Nfor a childhood friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.30,0:05:22.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I understand! I'll help!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.27,0:05:25.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I know we can make a great soccer ball cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.74,0:05:28.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you! You know how to make one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.71,0:05:31.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh... I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:35.45,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Then how are we going to make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.45,0:05:38.95,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but if we think it over,\NI'm sure it'll work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.46,0:05:49.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Counter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.26,0:05:53.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Really. Maybe I shouldn't have asked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:55.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now. I'm told that most invention
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.17,0:05:59.34,Main,,0,0,0,,only happens after a long series of failures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.34,0:06:01.71,Main,,0,0,0,,That's not very convincing\Ncoming from someone
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:05.68,Main,,0,0,0,,who does trial-and-error answers for\Ntests we already know the questions for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.85,0:06:09.91,Main,,0,0,0,,For instance, this.\NIt's about the way light reflects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.91,0:06:12.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"Class 2-C, #20\NName: Mari Hayase"\NFor instance, this.\NIt's about the way light reflects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.62,0:06:16.89,Main,,0,0,0,,"Class 2-C, #20\NName: Mari Hayase"\N"How does your face look\Nreflected in the mirror?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:17.06,Main,,0,0,0,,"How does your face look\Nreflected in the mirror?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:19.06,Main,,0,0,0,,The answer:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:20.96,Main,,0,0,0,,"It looks cute!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.96,0:06:25.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from? The answer\Nis "with left and right switched."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:27.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:32.84,Main,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe you're\Nthe daughter of a world-class scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.84,0:06:37.28,Main,,0,0,0,,By the way, is your father still away?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.28,0:06:38.88,Main,,0,0,0,,It's been three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.88,0:06:45.45,Main,,0,0,0,,But it seems taking aimless research trips\Nhas been his thing for a while, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.45,0:06:48.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if I'm gone, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:52.46,Main,,0,0,0,,This armillary compass\Nwill always show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.63,0:06:55.93,Main,,0,0,0,,That's what he told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:58.13,Main,,0,0,0,,But three years is a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.13,0:07:02.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, today's cake\Nwon't take that long, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.30,0:07:07.81,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll search the internet for how to make it,\Nso just follow the directions, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.81,0:07:10.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Search the internet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.71,0:07:14.35,Main,,0,0,0,,It's your idea! Let's think it over together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:16.95,Main,,0,0,0,,We should use the\Nknowledge of our predecessors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:21.25,Main,,0,0,0,,If everyone had to reinvent the wheel,\Ncivilization would never advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:23.59,Main,,0,0,0,,But... But Waka...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.26,0:07:26.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Who's winning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.39,0:07:27.83,Main,,0,0,0,,The next town over, I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.83,0:07:30.70,Main,,0,0,0,,But they sure can hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:35.67,Main,,0,0,0,,But you failed because you couldn't\Nfind out the right way to do it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.67,0:07:39.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hayase! Mizuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.57,0:07:41.54,Main,,0,0,0,,It's Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.54,0:07:42.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.85,0:07:54.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:58.12,Main,,0,0,0,,--Hey, Futa! You okay? Futa!\N--Futa?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:01.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Coach! Ichikawa is... Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.19,0:08:03.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa! Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.70,0:08:04.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.97,0:08:08.47,Main,,0,0,0,,What wrong, Ichikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:10.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.10,0:08:11.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:13.04,Main,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.04,0:08:16.04,Main,,0,0,0,,--A ball hit him, and then...\N--Futa...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.04,0:08:16.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Where did it hit him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.98,0:08:17.61,Main,,0,0,0,,The chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.61,0:08:19.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! Call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:21.88,Main,,0,0,0,,B-Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.88,0:08:24.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Ichikawa! Ichikawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.95,0:08:26.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't move him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.32,0:08:28.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:32.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Calm down. An AED... do you have an AED?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:35.63,Main,,0,0,0,,An... AED?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.63,0:08:36.53,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:37.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay. Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.37,0:08:47.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Not good. He's in cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.14,0:08:51.61,Main,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.61,0:08:53.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Five, six, seven, eight, nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:55.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:04.02,Main,,0,0,0,,An electric shock is necessary.\NPlease move away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:08.03,Main,,0,0,0,,There's going to be an electric shock.\NPlease move away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.03,0:09:10.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Press the closed circuit button firmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.56,0:09:12.83,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm closing the circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.83,0:09:15.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Checking status.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.97,0:09:21.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.01,0:09:22.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.11,0:09:25.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Further electric shock is not required.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:27.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-That hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:29.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:31.68,Main,,0,0,0,,M-Mizuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.68,0:09:34.55,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad... I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.55,0:09:37.89,Main,,0,0,0,,You... Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.36,0:09:47.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.70,0:09:50.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! Futa, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:53.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Why is she so mad at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.41,0:09:59.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Will he be okay, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.28,0:10:01.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.08,0:10:05.62,Main,,0,0,0,,It caused a ventricular fibrillation, and\Nsent him into temporary cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:06.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:09.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, you're so reliable!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:18.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I have cram school.\NTake care on the way home, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.50,0:10:20.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:21.70,Main,,0,0,0,,He's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.70,0:10:25.74,Main,,0,0,0,,You can tell he's a future med student\Nat the top of his class!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.74,0:10:27.41,Main,,0,0,0,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.41,0:10:31.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get to making that cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.81,0:10:33.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:36.05,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm borrowing your computer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.05,0:10:39.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's okay to go\Ninto Shun's room without asking?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:44.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I don't think he has\Nany dirty magazines or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.09,0:10:49.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you talking about? Of course\NShun wouldn't have those things!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.93,0:10:51.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:57.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, even if he did, he'd\Nprobably have them well-hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:58.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:10:59.34,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:05.01,Main,,0,0,0,,This book. I've seen it in Papa's lab before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:07.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Cake! Cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:19.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? It's all in English?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.96,0:11:23.96,Main,,0,0,0,,William... Gilbert...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.13,0:11:27.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at this, Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:31.74,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the recipe I used yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.74,0:11:34.07,Main,,0,0,0,,But that one didn't go well at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:12:00.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? H-Hey! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.00,0:12:03.47,Main,,0,0,0,,What on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.47,0:12:05.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.54,0:12:12.58,Main,,0,0,0,,S-S-Someone! S-Someone call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.28,0:12:18.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:22.09,Main,,0,0,0,,But anyway... speak to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:25.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Hello? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.29,0:12:28.26,Main,,0,0,0,,She's just like Futa. What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.26,0:12:32.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... what was that machine called? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:34.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:41.87,Main,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four, five, six, seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.87,0:12:43.71,Main,,0,0,0,,--eight, nine, ten!\N--Dr. Gilbert! This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.71,0:12:46.08,Main,,0,0,0,,--One, two, three, four, five,\N--Excuse me, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:48.85,Main,,0,0,0,,--six, seven, eight, nine, ten!\N--Make way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.85,0:12:53.85,Main,,0,0,0,,--One, two, three, four, five, six!\N--You! What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.85,0:12:55.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Move. I'll take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:57.19,Main,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.06,0:13:02.56,Main,,0,0,0,,This man. Is he...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:04.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Miss. Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:16.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Settle down. It's okay. I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.61,0:13:18.41,Main,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.41,0:13:20.51,Main,,0,0,0,,M-My head...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.51,0:13:23.58,Main,,0,0,0,,It looks like you hit it when you fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.58,0:13:27.42,Main,,0,0,0,,If it starts hurting very badly,\Nplease come by my clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.42,0:13:29.89,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.89,0:13:33.49,Main,,0,0,0,,That girl came out of thin air,\Nand I was so startled...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.49,0:13:37.96,Main,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry! Um... I'm really sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.20,0:13:40.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:42.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:46.34,Main,,0,0,0,,What happened? You called me so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.34,0:13:50.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari... Mari suddenly disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.04,0:13:52.01,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:57.35,Main,,0,0,0,,She was looking at that book...\Nthen suddenly, her body started shining...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.35,0:14:00.65,Main,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.65,0:14:03.82,Main,,0,0,0,,I understand. Anyway, try to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:04.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.96,0:14:08.06,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1600\N(What is now) London, England"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:11.46,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1600\N(What is now) London, England"\NI see. You're from the future, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.46,0:14:13.43,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. You're from the future, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.43,0:14:14.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.97,0:14:18.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Interesting! A truly intriguing story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.94,0:14:21.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Can you prove it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:23.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Prove it? I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:28.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:30.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.12,0:14:37.19,Main,,0,0,0,,But is this really London in the year 1600?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.19,0:14:39.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:42.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Forgive the late introduction.\NI am William Gilbert.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.53,0:14:45.13,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm a doctor, as well as a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.13,0:14:46.53,Main,,0,0,0,,A scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:50.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. This world is full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:54.81,Main,,0,0,0,,And there's much that human\Nknowledge does not yet know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.81,0:14:59.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I believe that bringing these things\Nto light and coming closer to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.51,0:15:03.15,Main,,0,0,0,,will lead us to a brilliant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.55,0:15:10.59,Main,,0,0,0,,What delicious clotted cream!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:13.19,Main,,0,0,0,,This really is England!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.19,0:15:17.50,Main,,0,0,0,,But you do speak fluent English.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:19.80,Main,,0,0,0,,English?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.80,0:15:22.90,Main,,0,0,0,,If you really came from the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:23.17,Main,,0,0,0,,--you must have found the principle that\Nmade it possible, and put it to use.\N-- I'm not speaking English...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:26.44,Main,,0,0,0,,--you must have found the principle that\Nmade it possible, and put it to use.\N-- I'm not speaking English...\N"English?"\N"But I don't speak English"\N"Isn't he speaking Japanese?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:30.01,Main,,0,0,0,,It's Dr. Gilbert who's\Nspeaking fluent Japanese.\N"English?"\N"But I don't speak English"\N"Isn't he speaking Japanese?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:34.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Humans can create whatever\Nthey imagine, after all.\N"English?"\N"But I don't speak English"\N"Isn't he speaking Japanese?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.61,0:15:38.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Did you say "create whatever they imagine"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.82,0:15:40.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.69,0:15:45.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-You don't know a researcher\Nnamed Eiji Hayase, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.39,0:15:52.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother! I think maybe\Nwe should call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:54.67,Main,,0,0,0,,No, if this book is the cause,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.67,0:15:58.17,Main,,0,0,0,,then Dr. Hayase's research may be involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:04.48,Main,,0,0,0,,My husband said he wanted\Nyou to have it, Shun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:06.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hayase did?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.48,0:16:11.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. He set out on\Na research trip so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:14.65,Main,,0,0,0,,But he wanted you to have that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:15.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"To Shun Mizuki"\NBut he wanted you to have that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:17.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"To Shun Mizuki"\N"To Shun Mizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.69,0:16:21.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I entrust this book to you\Nwhile I'm on my trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:28.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Keep it safe, and don't tell anyone about it\Nuntil you understand what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.33,0:16:31.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Eiji Hayase."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:34.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.77,0:16:36.34,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.34,0:16:39.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we should go to\NDr. Hayase's laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.78,0:16:40.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.75,0:16:43.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase? Is he Japanese, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.85,0:16:45.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.12,0:16:49.92,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know if he's the doctor\Nyou're speaking of,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.92,0:16:56.66,Main,,0,0,0,,but several months ago, I met a man\Nfrom the Orient who praised my research.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.66,0:16:58.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.60,0:17:00.10,Main,,0,0,0,,I fear I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.10,0:17:05.57,Main,,0,0,0,,He came out of nowhere when I was at\Nthe harbor hiring sailors for a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.57,0:17:08.64,Main,,0,0,0,,He mainly wanted a handshake, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:10.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.74,0:17:15.88,Main,,0,0,0,,But the words you said...\NI'm sure he said them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.05,0:17:20.89,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought it a perfect\Nphrase for a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:26.46,Main,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.46,0:17:31.06,Main,,0,0,0,,My father went missing three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.06,0:17:33.90,Main,,0,0,0,,The person you're talking about might be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.67,0:17:38.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.00,0:17:42.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Searching all alone in this\Nstrange land for your father...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.51,0:17:44.11,Main,,0,0,0,,It must have been hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.11,0:17:49.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much. I'm okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.08,0:17:53.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, what research\Nare you doing, Dr. Gilbert?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:56.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:18:00.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Right now, I'm experimenting to see\Nwhy a compass always points north.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:04.03,Main,,0,0,0,,I want to explain the mechanism\Nbehind it and offer proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.03,0:18:07.23,Main,,0,0,0,,What? That's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:12.47,Main,,0,0,0,,I suppose that mystery has already\Nbeen solved in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.47,0:18:16.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Mystery? But everybody knows that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.31,0:18:19.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Really? Then please tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:22.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Why does a compass needle point north?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:24.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.28,0:18:26.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Actually, why does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.82,0:18:29.89,Main,,0,0,0,,I've never even thought about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.89,0:18:33.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.19,0:18:34.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.66,0:18:39.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it,\NI don't actually know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:42.13,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.13,0:18:43.47,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:45.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.37,0:18:49.01,Main,,0,0,0,,There are various theories on the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:54.55,Main,,0,0,0,,For instance, this book says that\Nthe needle is pulled by the North Star.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:58.85,Main,,0,0,0,,That's true! The North Star is\Nalways in the northern sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.85,0:19:02.05,Main,,0,0,0,,But there's no proof of this theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.05,0:19:03.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:06.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. Without proof,\Nyou cannot be sure it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:13.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Some sailors believe that there's a huge\Nmagnetic mountain on the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.23,0:19:17.07,Main,,0,0,0,,But there's no solid proof of this, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.07,0:19:18.84,Main,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:24.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Well? Why not help me with\Nmy research while I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.01,0:19:28.88,Main,,0,0,0,,I can show you the way of thinking through\Nwhich the principles of nature are unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.88,0:19:32.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay! I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.95,0:19:37.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay. Then let's head out.\NIt's about time for them to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.39,0:19:40.26,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.26,0:19:41.63,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll see when we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.63,0:19:44.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.13,0:19:47.20,Main,,0,0,0,,To take her outside dressed like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.34,0:19:54.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh. Good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.24,0:19:56.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you have anything to put on her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.81,0:19:58.84,Main,,0,0,0,,One moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.65,0:20:03.85,Main,,0,0,0,,"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.85,0:20:05.35,Main,,0,0,0,,How do we get inside?\N"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:06.22,Main,,0,0,0,,How do we get inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:09.12,Main,,0,0,0,,It's somewhere around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.12,0:20:10.49,Main,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.26,0:20:12.56,Main,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:14.69,Main,,0,0,0,,The doctor's very lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.69,0:20:17.06,Main,,0,0,0,,He doesn't like carrying\Na lot of things around with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.06,0:20:20.40,Main,,0,0,0,,But then why even bother having security?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.08,0:20:36.75,Main,,0,0,0,,No use? The lights inside\Nmust have been shut off...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:39.72,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.72,0:20:42.92,Main,,0,0,0,,It's part of a lady's toilette!\NPlease try to bear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.92,0:20:48.59,Main,,0,0,0,,But still... if you draw it that tight...\NI c-can't breathe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.59,0:20:53.40,Main,,0,0,0,,But I can't believe you were walking\Naround in that obscene outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.40,0:20:57.57,Main,,0,0,0,,In this country, any lady would be\Nembarrassed to show her legs like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.57,0:21:02.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Would she? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.14,0:21:04.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.44,0:21:06.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Time out! Time out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.15,0:21:10.45,Main,,0,0,0,,That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.45,0:21:13.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I nearly died...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.22,0:21:15.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Forgive the wait, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:16.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.69,0:21:21.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.33,0:21:28.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.17,0:21:32.67,Main,,0,0,0,,B-Brother! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.61,0:21:38.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Is there something under here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:43.08,Main,,0,0,0,,You're the one who used to\Nhang out here. Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.08,0:21:45.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I never knew he had an underground room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.42,0:21:50.59,Main,,0,0,0,,And it seems to be on a\Ndifferent electrical system.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.59,0:21:54.06,Main,,0,0,0,,There must be a stairway to get down there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:57.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we can't do anything\Nunless we get down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.77,0:22:09.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.81,0:22:14.98,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Lights on at Hayase's laboratory?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.98,0:22:17.45,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.45,0:22:21.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Find the doctor and take him\Nquickly into custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.02,0:22:23.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's have as little fuss as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.99,0:22:26.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Finally back, are you, Eiji Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.06,0:22:29.93,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Sorrowful Gilbert"\NFinally back, are you, Eiji Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.95,0:24:00.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.62,0:24:02.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.92,0:24:04.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.02,0:24:08.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, you had trouble with Mr. Gilbert's\Nquestion before, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.29,0:24:10.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.96,0:24:13.43,Main,,0,0,0,,But everybody knows that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.43,0:24:16.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Really? Then please tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.10,0:24:19.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Why does a compass needle point north?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.27,0:24:21.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Actually, why does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.77,0:24:25.04,Main,,0,0,0,,I never even thought about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.04,0:24:31.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Being a scientist means doubting things\Nbelieved to be common knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.48,0:24:34.52,Main,,0,0,0,,But what will Mr. Gilbert do next?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.52,0:24:36.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka? When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.62,0:24:37.99,Main,,0,0,0,,I've been here the whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.99,0:24:43.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now. We'll find out what\NMr. Gilbert does next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.53,0:24:46.60,Main,,0,0,0,,In the meantime,\Nlet's have a little pre-study.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.60,0:24:48.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen this tool?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.80,0:24:50.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.37,0:24:54.44,Main,,0,0,0,,It looks kind of like a compass\Nstood up on its side...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.44,0:24:57.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, excellent observation!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.91,0:24:59.81,Main,,0,0,0,,See? When you do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.81,0:25:01.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Ah! It is a compass!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.78,0:25:05.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I had a feeling that's what it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.22,0:25:08.89,Main,,0,0,0,,The principle is that a\Ncompass turned on its side,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.89,0:25:12.99,Main,,0,0,0,,in other words, perpendicular to\Nthe ground, is called a dip circle,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.99,0:25:18.06,Main,,0,0,0,,and it's a device for measuring the angle\Nbetween the horizon and the north pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.06,0:25:20.10,Main,,0,0,0,,But Doctor, what's it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.10,0:25:21.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.10,0:25:23.87,Main,,0,0,0,,That's what you'll find out next week!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.87,0:25:26.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa, is this segment just\Na next episode preview?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.84,0:25:29.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, not exactly...
